<p>Solve the equation given below by factoring. <me>$generalForm = 0</me></p>





<!--*********************************************
            Graphing Tool
**********************************************-->

<aside><title>Graphing tool</title>

<setup>
  <number name="ymin">min($k - 10, -10)</number>
  <number name="xmin">min($r - 10, $s - 10, -10)</number>
  <number name="ymax">max($k + 10, 10)</number>
  <number name="xmax">max($r + 10, $s + 10, 10)</number>
  <number name="zeroFixed" fixed>0</number>
</setup>
  
<sideBySide margins="5%" widths="30% 70%">
<div>
<p>The left-hand side of the given equation is  <mathInput name="eqLHS"/></p>
<p>The righ-hand side of the given equation is  <mathInput name="eqRHS"/></p>
<p>A <em>graphical</em> solution consists in observing the locations, if any, where the graph of the equation <m>y = $eqLHS</m> <em>intersects</em> the graph of <m>y = $eqRHS</m></p>

</div>

<div>
<graph name="g1" ymin="$ymin{link='false'}" ymax="$ymax{link='false'}" xmin="$xmin{link='false'}" xmax="$xmax{link='false'}">
  <function name="givenParabola">$eqLHS</function>
  <line name="rhsLine" styleNumber="8">y = $eqRHS</line>
  <point name="p1" styleNumber="5">($graphSolX1, $eqRHS)</point>
  <point name="p2" styleNumber="5">($graphSolX2, $eqRHS)</point>
</graph>

</div> 
</sideBySide>

<p>Graph the solutions you determined by factoring (only input one value for one solution, no values for no solutions):</p>
<p><m>x = </m> <mathInput name="graphSolX1"/> or <m>x = </m> <mathInput name="graphSolX2"/></p>
  
<p><alert>Tip:</alert> You can use the graphical solution as a check on your work, but make sure you work out the algebra by factoring the trinomial as well!</p>

</aside>  


<!--*********************************************
            Solution input
**********************************************-->
<p>First, the number of solutions is: <choiceInput name="numSols" inline>
  <choice>1</choice>
  <choice>2</choice>
  <choice>No solutions</choice>
</choiceInput></p>
  
<conditionalContent>
  <case condition="$numSols.selectedIndices = 1">
    <p><m>x = </m> <mathInput name="xSol1"/></p>
  </case>
  <case condition="$numSols.selectedIndices = 2">
    <p><m>x = </m> <mathInput name="xSol2a"/> or <m>x = </m><mathInput name="xSol2b"/></p>
  </case>
</conditionalContent>

<answer name="ans1" unorderedCompare hide="$numSols.selectedIndices != 1 and $numSols.selectedIndices != 2 and $numSols.selectedIndices != 3">
    <award><when>$oneCorrect</when></award>
    <award><when>$twoCorrect</when></award>
</answer>




